.TH ANYA 1 "March 2026" "anya 0.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
anya \- fast static malware analysis tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anya
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B anya verse
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B anya
performs static analysis on binary files (PE, ELF) to identify suspicious
characteristics without executing them.
It calculates cryptographic hashes, Shannon entropy, extracts strings, parses
PE and ELF structures, maps findings to MITRE ATT&CK techniques, and produces
a risk score.
.PP
All analysis is performed locally. No network access is required or initiated.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B verse
Print a random Bible verse (NLT) and exit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Analyse a single file.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-directory\fR \fIDIR\fR
Analyse all recognised executables in a directory (batch mode).
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
Recursively descend into subdirectories (requires \fB\-\-directory\fR).
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
Output analysis as JSON instead of formatted text.
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fIFILE\fR
Write output to \fIFILE\fR instead of stdout.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-append\fR
Append to output file instead of overwriting (requires \fB\-\-output\fR).
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show additional detail in text output.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress all output except warnings and errors.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable coloured terminal output.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-min\-string\-length\fR \fILENGTH\fR
Override the minimum string length for extraction (default: 4).
.TP
\fB\-\-guided\fR
Show contextual malware-analysis lessons after each file (Teacher Mode).
.TP
\fB\-\-init\-config\fR
Write a default config file to the user config directory and exit.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Use a custom config file instead of the default.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Default config location:
.TP
Linux/macOS:
\fI~/.config/anya/config.toml\fR
.TP
Windows:
\fI%APPDATA%\\anya\\config.toml\fR
.PP
Create the default config with \fBanya \-\-init\-config\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Analysis error, file not found, or unsupported format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Analyse a single PE file:
.B anya \-\-file suspicious.exe
.TP
Output JSON to a file:
.B anya \-\-file malware.dll \-\-json \-\-output report.json
.TP
Batch scan recursively:
.B anya \-\-directory ./samples \-\-recursive \-\-json \-\-output batch.jsonl \-\-append
.TP
Print a verse:
.B anya verse
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation: \fIhttps://github.com/elementmerc/anya\fR
.br
JSON output schema: \fIhttps://github.com/elementmerc/anya/blob/master/JSON_SCHEMA.md\fR
